title: Workspace Management
slug: workspaces
description: Isolated workspaces with per-workspace config, tools, and file systems.
order: 14
features:
  - name: Workspace Lifecycle
    status: implemented
    description: >
      Create, switch, import, and export workspaces. Each workspace has isolated OPFS
      storage, conversation history, tool permissions, agent definitions, and config.
      Lazy panel rendering defers non-essential DOM until first navigation.
    source_files:
      - web/clawser-workspace-lifecycle.js
      - web/clawser-state.js

  - name: Workspace Config
    status: implemented
    description: >
      Per-workspace settings — autonomy level, model overrides, cache TTL, cost caps,
      and tool permissions. Config sections render eagerly since they affect runtime
      behavior on load.
    source_files:
      - web/clawser-state.js

  - name: Import/Export
    status: implemented
    description: >
      Export workspaces as JSON bundles including config, conversations, memories, and
      agent definitions. Import from bundle to create a new workspace or merge into existing.
    source_files:
      - web/clawser-workspace-lifecycle.js
